PN,31705
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1775782987
OL,3,CEmperor penguins and Antarctic fur
OL,4,Cseals face extinction due to climate
OL,5,Cchange
OL,7,FThe number of mature seals has fallen
OL,8,Ffrom an estimated 2,187,000 in 1999 to
OL,9,F944,000 in 2025 as rising ocean
OL,10,Ftemperatures and shrinking sea ice
OL,11,Fpush krill, a major food source, to
OL,12,Fgreater ocean depths in search of
OL,13,Fcolder water.
OL,15,FIn South Georgia, an island north of
OL,16,FAntarctica in the Atlantic Ocean,
OL,17,Fkrill shortages have dramatically
OL,18,Freduced the survival of seal pups in
OL,19,Ftheir first year, leading to an ageing
OL,20,Fbreeding population, the experts said.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
